claim: The Kingdom of England was the most powerful nation in Europe after the end of the Civil War in 1660.
premise_source_doc_sentence: With an increasingly centralized monarchy , the first standing army since Roman times , and the use of artillery , France expelled the English from its territory and came out of the Middle Ages as the most powerful nation in Europe , only to lose that status to the Holy Roman Empire and Spain following defeat in the Italian Wars .
